mongod --version --> To get the version of mongodb.
brew list --versions mongodb-community --> List all versions of mongodb installed in your system.
brew services list --> Shows the status of mongodb in your system.
brew install mongodb-community@5.0 --> This will install a specific version of mongodb in your system.

To start and stop the services use these:
brew services start mongodb-community@6.0
brew services stop mongodb-community@6.0

mongosh -> This will open the shell where you can execute the commands and check your databases.

Mongosh commands:

1. db -> This will show all the db/collections in your system.
2. show dbs -> Shows all the database you have
3. use db -> This will create a new db with the name db.
